The paper discusses properties of fuzzy information systems and homomorphisms, which are concepts related to logic and artificial intelligence (cs.LO, cs.AI). The classification of consistent functions and the characterization of fuzzy relation mappings involve mathematical concepts such as functions and relations, which are also relevant to discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The paper also mentions the use of information theory in some of the properties presented (cs.IT), and the application of homomorphisms in data mining (cs.SI).
